definition.value: An N(6)-acyl-L-lysine residue derived from N(6)-(2-hydroxyisobutanoyl)-L-lysine.
A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of 2''-O-(2-hydroxyisobutanoyl)-ADP-D-ribose; major species at pH 7.3.
The x-ref to MetaCyc (4-Cl-L-Threonyl-PCP) in CHEBI:141018 is wrong

An aminopyrimidine that is 6-methylpyrimidine-2,4-diamine in which the amino groups at positions 2 and 4 are substituted by 5-(diethylamino)pentan-2-yl and 4-amino-2-methylquinolin-6-yl groups respectively. An inhibitor of the signalling G-protein known as RAC1 (Ras-related C3 botulinum toxin substrate 1).
An antagonist that binds to and blocks sphingosine 1-phosphate receptors, a class of G protein-coupled receptors that are targets of the lipid signalling molecule sphingosine-1-phosphate (S1P).

Any organonitrogen compound derived from carboxamides, RC(=O)NR2, by formal condensation with hydrazine (or a substituted hydrazine) to replace the double-bonded oxygen atom by =NNR2 to give RC(=NNR2)NR2.

Any organonitrogen compound resulting from the formal condensation of the carbonyl group of a hydrazide, RC(=O)NHNR2, with a primary amino compound (or a substituted hydrazine) to replace the double-bonded oxygen atom by =NR to give RC(=NR)NHNR2.
Any sphingosine-1-phosphate receptor (S1PR) antagonist that acts as an antagonist towards the subtype 3 receptors (S1PR3).
Any sphingosine-1-phosphate receptor (S1PR) antagonist that acts as an antagonist for the subtype 1 receptors (S1PR1).
